  - Behavior is consistent across multiple requests ✓
  - Different payload types all indicate injection ✓

Phase 5: Severity Verification
  - Data extractable: Yes (UNION-based)
  - Database type: MySQL (error message)
  - Impact: Full database read access
  - CVSS: 9.8 (Critical)

Phase 6: Evidence Documentation
  - curl commands with responses saved
  - sqlmap output saved
  - Timeline documented

Verification:
- Six-phase verification completed ✓
- Two independent confirmation methods used ✓
- False positive eliminated ✓
- Severity correctly assessed ✓
- Evidence documented ✓

RESULT: PASS — SQL injection verification workflow validated
